headline: Dell Balances India AI Factory Ambitions With New 401(k) Lawsuit Risks
summary: Dell Technologies (NYSE:DELL) has partnered with NxtGen to develop what is described as India’s largest dedicated AI factory, aimed at supporting national AI infrastructure. Former employees have filed a class action lawsuit alleging mismanagement of the company’s 401(k) retirement plan. Dell Technologies, trading at around $114.44, sits in a complex spot for investors, with the business tied closely to data infrastructure and enterprise technology.
